She knows now that validation for girls must come through themselves, but she remembers a time when being affirmed wasn’t so easy:

She struggled to find people—a mother, a father, a boyfriend—once school became schoolwork and boys.

“I had no idea what I’d do with my life. In our society, we’re so sheltered and don’t know how to move forward, so we break down internally. It’s a lot.”

Zorion has had some help with finding her purpose. Her grandmother pays for a private tutor for her math and science. She also has a wonderful support system with her friends and family—a community to whom
